							<h2>Game Overview</h2>
							<p>Junk Busters is an Android mobile game that challenges players to clean up space debris by navigating a spaceship through an asteroid field. The game combines quick reflexes with strategic planning as players collect space junk while avoiding dangerous objects. This project demonstrated my ability to apply core programming concepts to interactive entertainment.</p>
							
							<h2>Development Technology</h2>
							<p>The game was developed using several key technologies:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Java</strong> - Primary programming language for Android development</li>
								<li><strong>Android SDK</strong> - Framework for creating mobile applications</li>
								<li><strong>LibGDX</strong> - Game development framework for handling graphics and input</li>
								<li><strong>Box2D</strong> - Physics engine for realistic object interactions</li>
							</ul>
							
							<h2>Game Features</h2>
							<p>Junk Busters included several engaging gameplay elements:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Progressive difficulty system that increases challenge over time</li>
								<li>Power-up mechanics that provide temporary abilities (shields, speed boosts, etc.)</li>
								<li>Score tracking and local leaderboard functionality</li>
								<li>Varied enemy types with different movement patterns</li>
								<li>Particle effects for visual feedback on collisions and achievements</li>
								<li>Sound effects and background music to enhance immersion</li>
							</ul>
							
							<h2>Technical Challenges</h2>
							<p>During development, I overcame several technical hurdles:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Implementing smooth, responsive controls for different screen sizes</li>
								<li>Optimizing collision detection to maintain consistent frame rates</li>
								<li>Managing game state and object lifecycles efficiently</li>
								<li>Balancing difficulty progression to create an engaging player experience</li>
								<li>Ensuring compatibility across various Android device specifications</li>
							</ul>
							
							<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>
							<p>This project provided valuable experience in several areas:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Object-oriented programming principles applied to game development</li>
								<li>Game loop architecture and frame-based animation</li>
								<li>Asset management and resource optimization for mobile platforms</li>
								<li>User experience design for interactive applications</li>
								<li>Testing and debugging techniques for real-time applications</li>
								<li>Project planning and incremental development methodology</li>
							</ul>
